[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'jamesfalkner', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2019-04-05 18:51:28+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'At https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-orm-panache-guide there is a snippet for streams:

```
List<String> namesButEmmanuels = Person.streamAll()
    .map(p -> p.name.toLowerCase() )
    .filter( n -> ! "emmanuel".equals(n) )
    .collect(Collectors.toList());
```

But it doesn't work due to no type information for the stream. It needs to be

```
List<String> namesButEmmanuels = Person.<Person>streamAll()
    .map(p -> p.name.toLowerCase() )
    .filter( n -> ! "emmanuel".equals(n) )
    .collect(Collectors.toList());
```

Thanks to @username_1 for the help!', 'title': 'Panache streams example not quite right', 'type': 'issue'}
